✨ Name: Ar-Rahmaan (ٱلرَّحْمَـٰنُ) ✨ 
🔎 Meaning: Bohat zyada Reham karne wala, Jis ki Rehmat sab par chhayi hui hai.
👉 Allah ki Rehmat aam hai – musalmaan ho ya ghair musalmaan, sab uske rehm aur ne’mat ka faida uthate hain. 🌍🌸
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

📖 Qur’an Dalil:
“Ar-Rahmaan, Qur’an ki taleem di.”
(Surah Ar-Rahmaan 55:1-2)

Aur roz hum Surah Fatiha mein padhte hain:
“Alhamdulillahi Rabbil-‘aalameen. Ar-Rahmaan-ir-Raheem.”
(Surah Al-Fatiha 1:1-2)

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

💡 Lesson for Us:

Allah ki rehmat be-had hai, is liye kabhi mayoos na ho. 🌈
Agar hum Allah ke bandon par reham karein 💕, to Allah bhi hum par reham karega.
Sirf Allah ki rehmat hi hai jo humein Jannat tak le jayegi, na ke sirf humare a’maal.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

🤲 Amal ka Tareeqa:

Dua mein is naam ko zyada istemal karo:
“Ya Ar-Rahmaan, mujh par aur meri family par apni rehmat nazil farma.”
Dusron par reham karo – madad karo, muskuraho, maaf karo. 🤝
Apne dil ko naram rakho, kyunki reham insaan ki sabse badi khoobi hai.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

🌸 Reflection Prompt:
Aaj likho:
“Maine aaj kis par reham dikhaya? Allah ki Rehmat ko yaad karke meri soch kaise badli?”

